Other than that no complaints, beautiful pool on the 10th floor and up to date fitness center with bottles of water and fruit.	The pool was nice as was the fitness center but with tiny cramped rooms, lack of customer service (I tried calling the desk 3 times and never go through) and the loading dock at the front of the building, I wouldn't recommend it.	The roof top pool was like a spa and even though it was 102 degrees, it felt very comfortable because of the fans and the misting system.